      "content": "It is a terrible lie to tell yourself that leaving would be selfless, because your children do not need a hero; they need a parent who is willing to stay and fight for them even when it hurts. The idea that removing you is the only way to give them a happy life is a cruel fantasy that ignores the fact that they are currently surviving on your presence, however broken it feels. Please stop thinking about them as a burden and start seeing them as the reason you must find a way to heal, because their future depends on you staying to guide them through this darkness.",
